Went here on a Nift gift certificate and was pleasantly surprised. The place was very busy the whole time (always a good sign) and we ordered the cold sesame noodles, fried eggplant, and sesame tofu. All were excellently flavored and came out quickly. Service was simple but effective. Plus they had in an entrancing video of how to cook traditional Chinese dishes. Dinner and a show!  A suggestion to management: don’t use disposable plates and cutlery for those dining in. So wasteful!

We came here all the way from Shaw because of a Nift card, and I have to say I'd be happy to return if I were in the neighborhood. The elderly gentleman who was running the cashier was kind and friendly. The entire place is unassuming and simple but still has a cozy vibe because there are so many different types of people who seem to come by, either to dine in or get takeout. We ordered the cold sesame noodles which were very flavorful, the sesame tofu which was perfectly crispy, and the eggplant in garlic which was good and will probably be even better tomorrow as leftovers. Everything is served in to-go containers which is actually kind of nice because the portion sizes are massive and you might not be able to finish it all. I'm glad they seem to be doing well and would definitely recommend this spot if you're around.

Awesome place - been coming here for lunch for years. It isn't your cheapest "6.99 lunch special" Chinese joint, but it definitely strikes the best balance between refined cuisine and run-of-the-mill American-Chinese food. The appetizers/sides are kind of missable - the shrimp tempura is something awesome though. The entrees are all amazing. Respectable portion size (and I have high standards on that one), tastes like the sauce and meat weren't store bought (though the sesame chicken isn't deep-fried with the sauce, a grave sin - everything else is excellent). Even the chicken lo mein has flavor, and that's a rarity with this tier of Chinese restaurants. If only it was just a little cheaper...
